Specification for `compressor.py` — the middle-out compression engine, stage 2 of the pipeline. Reads a CompressionJob from stdin, emits a CompressionResult to stdout.

# read ../orchestrator-go/main.go

The incoming message is the `CompressionJob` emitted by the orchestrator. Read its struct definition and mirror the exact field names — do not guess the shape.

# entity CompressionResult {#compression_result}

The result message — the input contract of `renderer-ts`.

## field request_id

Copied verbatim from the incoming job.

## field source_service

Constant string `compression-py`.

## field algorithm

Constant string `middle-out-rle-v1`.

## field original_size_bytes

Integer: UTF-8 byte length of the incoming `payload`.

## field compressed_payload

String produced by `compress_middle_out` {#compress_middle_out}.

## field compression_ratio

Float, rounded to two decimals: `original_size_bytes / len(compressed_payload)`.

# func compress_middle_out {#compress_middle_out}

The proprietary algorithm: run-length encoding that works outward from the middle of the input — the two halves are encoded from the center toward the edges.

## arg text

Non-empty `str` — the job payload.

## result

`str` — `"<left>|<right>"`, where `left` is the RLE of the first half read right-to-left (from the middle outward) and `right` is the RLE of the second half read left-to-right. RLE encodes each run as the character followed by its decimal count, e.g. `aaab` → `a3b1`.

# func main {#compressor_main}

## flow

1. Read all of stdin and parse it as JSON.
2. If the message is the shared error envelope from upstream, log an `ERROR` line with its code, forward the envelope to stdout verbatim, and exit `1`.
3. If parsing fails, or `request_id` / `payload` is missing, or `payload` is not a non-empty string, emit `PP_BAD_JOB` and stop.
4. Log acceptance with the request id.
5. Compress the payload with `compress_middle_out` {#compress_middle_out}.
6. Build the `CompressionResult` {#compression_result} and write it to stdout as a single line.
7. Log emission (request id and compression ratio) and exit `0`.

## error PP_BAD_JOB

Raised on malformed or incomplete input. Emit the shared error envelope with this code, `source_service` set to `compression-py`, the incoming `request_id` when one was readable (otherwise empty string), and exit `1`.
